entries.femaleVariant: I want a perimeter.
Betcha didn't expect to see me here.
Be more than glad to.
You screwed me on this, almost got me killed. That wasn't a financial tracer.
I fucked you over, you fucked the gang over. Somewhere at the start of the story, somebody fucked the corp.
See how this works, now? Ultimately, the corp gets what it wants.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="mamita" b="Time we were on our way, " a="."/>
entries.maleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="carnal" b="Time we were on our way, " a="."/>

entries.femaleVariant: Mature. Real mature…
Yeah, maybe.
You tricked me.
Fuck you.
Remember that. Learn it. And maybe a couple years down the line, you'll be standing where I am.
Till next time, then, V. Corporate gods willing.
Secure the area!
Thought you'd never see me again, didn't ya?
Naive little punk.
Yeah, maybe.
But you'll have to learn to follow orders first.
Then you'll need to get good. And make it possible. Next time.
Yeaaaah. Had enough for one day, lemme tell you.
Let Dex know we got his toy for him. Fatso oughta crack open a bottle for us after what we did for him today.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Ahí luego" b="" a=", V."/>
That the Militech bitch...?
Militech. They got those things buzzin' around everywhere.
Mhm...
It's over.
Think we're done. That's it.
Fuck you, cunt. That's for your trickery.
I keep my word.
When I say something, I do it, keep my word.
Mhm. Me too.
Heard one of the Flatheads is missing. Must've fallen off the truck along the way. Guess Militech'll never find it.
Been there.
Been there, Stout. Seen it, done it.
Today, you're a winner. But it don't mean a thing, and you don't mean a thing.
You're a dog on a leash. You get treats, hear nice things, all in prep for the day when your masters'll whore you out 'cause it's convenient. Honestly, I feel sorry for you.
Oh, thought about what you said. About convoys, transport security. Your offer?
We're just not interested.
We don't want any trouble.
Mhm... So what now?
We don't want any more trouble.
So what now?
Today was about Royce getting his just desserts.
No, I seriously doubt you do.
Maybe I should look into exactly what you did here…
Couldn't have done it without you. Flathead's yours, and consider us even.
Y'know, I like the way you operate. Maybe you'd do some more work for us?
Dunno. That's not always possible. And I'm not that great at it, anyway.
entries.maleVariant: Dunno. That's not always possible. And I'm not great at it, anyway.

entries.femaleVariant: Pleasure doing business.
Keep telling yourself that.
Fine. But maybe you'd be interested in the identity of your mole? How they put it all together?
OK. Talk.
Your problem's on the state line. Cargo manifests were stamped LOA. Merch was then "lost" just after it crossed the border.
Inside job by a man you know – Anthony Gilchrist.
Well, I see I'm working with a professional.
You won't regret this. This is going to be seriously rewarding for you, count on it.
I know the mole's identity.
No biggie.
Not my thing anyway.
Mhm...
Mhm. Militech don't forgive, Militech don't forget.
entries.maleVariant: Militech don't forgive, Militech don't forget.

entries.femaleVariant: Good work, Jack.
Thanks, Jack. Solid as ever.
Hey, yeah, you too, but uh... Hey, what's this about? You feelin' all right?
Yeah, wanna make sure… you know. We're good together. I like how we do things.
I do too, V. I do too.
'Ey, let Dex know we got his toy for him. And then I say we hit the Afterlife, hahaha... You know, do some shots.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Ahí luego" b="" a=", V."/>
Acquaintance of yours?
Yep. Familiar face from my past life.
Holy shit, V. Wasn't sure we'd walk out in one piece.
Running away? That's rich.
I knew her.
